choices.text: Given a string, if the cursor is at the front of the line, then pressing a  <  (the  Backspace  key) does nothing. If the cursor is at the back of the line, then pressing a  [  (the  Home  key) does nothing. If the cursor is at the end of the line, then pressing a  ]  (the  End  key) does nothing. For all other valid character in the input, it actually means that the corresponding key is pressed, we insert that character at the (typing) cursor position, and advance one position to the right the cursor accordingly.
